Although the advertised trivia night had been cancelled and the food was subpar, well enjoyed ourselves because of the familiar environment. We have gone to Sunset for years and it’s been an integral part of our experience here at BU. We explained to her that it was just a typo and that we were sincerely sorry for the mixup and that she could correct to receipt to the proper tip of 20 percent. She remained very rude and not grateful or understanding at all, left us outside, and came back to taunt us again saying “don’t ever come back”. The worst service I’ve ever received. Oh, Sunset! Unfortunately, this is one of the only halfway decent restaurants left on Comm Ave. We go here occasionally for lunch at work and only do so if we don't have 1PM meetings because if we do we know we won't make it back in time. We always make sure we have food and drink orders ready when the waitperson comes by the first time because you never know when they might come back. Food is decent, service is extremely lacking.  They recently changed ownership, but in doing so changed the menu getting rid of all of the lunch specials and now charge more for basically the same food. They also killed all of the fun margs on the drink menu.  Some key experiences: One time my friend got his card charged $1800 because the waitress forgot the decimal point when entering in his $18.00 check. Luckily he had the funds but his account was basically on hold waiting for the refund to go through.  There have been numerous times when we haven't even received our drinks until 12:30 or later when arriving for lunch at 12.  Constantly forgetting sides, parts of your order, drinks, etc.  We want to love Sunset, we really do but we've been so scarred by them we aren't sure we ever really will.

The food isn't good but the environment is great
Lots of menu options. The quesadillas are yummy. A little bit pricy, but a lot of food comes with the entree.

Not the place this used to be. The draft beer list used to offer lots of interesting beers in many styles, now it's very unimaginative. The nachos are the only thing worth ordering and they're quite expensive. Don't order the steak enchiladas. Our server was giving it a good try, but his recommendation of that dish was disappointing. This place only survives because of the BU students and the Agganis stadium across the street. We will not return.

Good ambience. Very good food. Excellent cocktails and margaritas. I was here with my friends celebrating Friday, and we had a blast. The portion size was decent, and prices reasonable. I would recommend the loaded nachos, they were delicious. The waitress served us long island on special request even though they didn't have it on the menu. Customer service 100/100. Highly recommend this spot!
This place is awesome.  The ribs are the great, and the staff is knows there cocktails
What joke Stay clear

Food was actually pretty good.  Unfortunately the service was horrible.  We waited over 30 min after ordering before we got anything.  They said they were understaffed, but yet people that came after we ordered had food on their table.  Come on.  In addition we had to constantly flag the waiter to get refills on drinks or anything.  They definitely didn’t deserve the 18% tip they racked onto the bill because of the large party.

Good restaurant, wish they had more vegan options. Mexican Cuisine is very easy to make vegan because there's a lot of simple options like rice and beans that could pass as entrees for those not consuming flesh of others voluntarily. The veggie burger is great! Made with quinoa, veggies, and mushrooms and great with a simple lettuce/tomato/onion pairing.
Great place. Was in the area for a hockey game and saw this place on Google.  Really glad we stopped here. Shout out to Tyler the bartender,  fantastic service!
1. The nachos are HUGE. Like ungodly large. 2. The beers are cheap. 3. Tyler is probably the best bartender I've ever had.

Someone from the kitchen dropped off our app and the waiter never came back. We would have ordered dinner and another round of drinks but oh well. They were too busy for our money that night. At least the nachos were good.

I wish I could rate this place a zero for their ineptitude and the manager's lack of concern for the well-being of his customers. This has been the WORST restaurant experience of my entire life. I came here looking to get drinks and food. …

I used to love the food at this place but it's gone completely downhill. The food tonight was awful, the service took forever, and after we informed the server of a food allergy they served us the wrong dish. Luckily we caught it before the person with the allergy ate it. Oh, and they tried to charge us twice for the food that was their mistake, so we had to ask them to take the extra charge off. They didn't offer any apologies or discount for trying to kill one of us. I'm done with this place, I don't care how many beers they have on draft.
Food = meh.  Staff = uninterested.
Great place to sit down, but I usually grab an order to go. Always fast, reasonable price, and wide selection of choices. Chicken Fajita Burrito Bowl To Go.

Very busy and understaffed. All wait staff and bartenders running around like mad men, forgetting orders and disappearing for 20 min at a time. College-like atmosphere. Ordered a nicer quality tequila and was sneakily poured bottom shelf. I know my tequila. Very disappointed over all. Don't recommend
Amazing atmosphere, and great vegetarian options
Mudslide Pie was amazing!
Good food. Superb service.

Your classic Mexican-inspired watering hole mostly centered around college students. The drinks are great and not overpriced and the food portions are huge and most things are incredibly delicious. I've had a great variety ranging from the nachos, to the chicken sandwich, to the fried cheesecake! (SO GOOD). Overall every experience here has been awesome with friendly staff and consistent food. Definitely a good spot to grab a drink with friends (especially if you "work out" next door at gymit and don't really care about how many calories are in a margarita)
Great nachos and good selection of beer
Unbelievable!! Service and the food was first class! Very reasonable prices. Found my new hangout spot.

Might be good to have a beer and watch the game, but the food and service wasnt great. Went there for lunch with a party of six. College was out so there was no wait to be seated. There had to have been 25 wait staff on to cover the maybe 20 people there. Service was very slow, beer came out gradually over a 15 minute period. We ordered an app and made the mistake of ordering our food along with it. The app came out quick, but was chased out five minutes later with out food. The app was OK, but the food was warm at best and tasteless. The waiter never came back, they were all huddle between the bar and the kitchen talking. We had to flag the waiter down for the bill. The bill was 147 with tip, not worth it.

I had a pretty rough brunch experience at this place over the weekend. I ordered a breakfast burrito and it was very mediocre.  It was served cold, especially the side of potatoes, and lacked any taste.  A couple of my friends had eggs benedict and their eggs were fully cooked instead of poached.  This leads me to believe the chef doesn't know what a poached egg is.  I also ordered two bloody mary's and was surprised that I was charged $9 for the second bloody mary.  The first bloody mary was $2.50, and i really would have appreciated a heads up from the waitress that the second bloody mary was not included in the brunch deal and is charged at full price.  She easily could have mentioned this when she asked me if I wanted a second bloody mary.  Also, upon receiving our checks, gratuity was added in.  I don't have a problem with this, but the waitress made no mention that this was added in and we almost double tipped her.  They added in a "surcharge" on the bill instead of clearly labeling it as gratuity. Overall, the food here is not very good and I left feeling like I had been cheated.
They have good food and good drinks
Alcohol is fair price, and the nachos are supposedly great. (I don't like cheese).

Nachos weren't that great but maybe they were just hyped up in my mind I mean they're nachos they were good and I ate em but people talk about their nachos like they're the best I thought they were decent. Great drinks.
Great service.   Good Mexican food.
Great food and atmosphere.
Nachos are to die for. Their weekend brunch is great too, $2.50 for bloody Mary's and mimosas!
OK place with good cocktails. The food was alright.
Great food, service, attentive staff!
Great environment for small or bigger companies, spacious tables, the best margaritas in the city, delicious nachos with cheese, no need to reserve in advance!!!! i love this place!

Sunset Cantina, Sunset Grill & Tap, and Patrons all have a similar menu and atmosphere, with Cantina being my personal choice. An enormous menu of fajitas, tacos, enchiladas, and salads paired with a huge selection of beers, Cantina is a fantastic choice for informal Mexican food. Parking in the garage behind the restaurant is free with validated parking ticket.

I've been going to the Sunset Cantina for the better part of the last 12 years and have consistently had great food and beer. The boneless subatomic wings are my favorite but the loaded potato skins are a close second. There's a great energetic vibe in the restaurant and we've never had to wait long for a table.
